x4codes.hlp: Off-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: yields have been measured proton-induced fission of
natural Uranium. Proton beams of 25 and 50 MeV
energies, and beam intensity of 1-4 uA were used. The
energy loss in the target was 1 MeV and 0.6 MeV for
25 MeV and 50 MeV protons, respectively. The target
was thin enough that the fission induced neutrons
could not thermalize in it. The recoiling fission
products leaving the target foil were stopped in He
buffer gas, where their charge state reduced to +1.
The collected fission products were then transported
by the gas flow to a differential pumping section,
where a sextupole ion beam guide directed them
into a magnetic mass separator. The selected ions
were then accumulated in a linear quadrupole
radiofrequency cooler and buncher. Finally, the
collected ion bunch was released into a double
Penning trap. Ions were counted with a microchannel
plate detector located at the ground potential
Corrections due to radioactive decay and count rate
fluctuations were applied to the experimental
yields. Isotopic yield distributions were fitted with
a Gaussian. The reported yields are normalised so
that the height of the Gaussian fit for each isotopic
